    {
      "slug": "process-remix",
      "title": "REMIX",
      "summary": "Gather references, constraints, and the real problem.",
      "tags": [
        "process"
      ],
      "links": [],
      "body": "Start wide: collect references, talk to people, map constraints and the actual job-to-be-done. Computational tools augment the search — scraping, clustering, moodboarding — but the goal is a sharp problem statement before a single pixel."
    },
    {
      "slug": "process-re-think",
      "title": "RE-THINK",
      "summary": "Make the roughest thing that proves the idea, then tighten it.",
      "tags": [
        "process"
      ],
      "links": [],
      "body": "Build the crudest artifact that can be felt: a clickable sketch, a shader toy, a paper cut-out. Optimize for learning per hour, not polish — the prototype's only job is to kill or confirm the direction. Once the idea holds, obsess over the invisible details: spacing, easing, contrast, the half-pixel. This is where craft lives."
    },
    {
      "slug": "process-re-imagine",
      "title": "RE:IMAGINE",
      "summary": "Get it in front of people; measure; re-open the loop.",
      "tags": [
        "process"
      ],
      "links": [],
      "body": "Ship to learn. Instrument it, watch real use, and treat launch as the start of the loop, not the end. What comes back from real hands is the feedback signal that re-opens the remix."
    },
